The speed of the courts/balls are LUDICROUSLY SLOW. It should be tennis, not a war of attrition. If you want wrestling there are a lot of options out there.

You knew from the first set, that Rafa was up against it. Struggling to counter the brutal power of Thiem. He tried all the tricks in his repertoire, including high topspin to Thiem's single hander. But to no avail.

A potential Djokovic-Thiem final would be an absolute slug-fest. Unlike Rafa though, Thiem would find it hard to counter the depth of Novak's shots.

snippet.textDisplay: First, congrats Dominic, what a nice job keeping yourself composed to pull it off. Secondly, I read the headline of an article in ESPN that read: Can Thiem "Upset" Nadal?  Nadal has already had very entertaining battles with Nadal, beating him on clay even.  At this point, I feel strongly that as much of a legend Nadal, Roger, Djoker et al are, there has to be a change of guard at some point, right. Just like Roger, Nadal, Djoker displaced Sampras, Kuerten, etc.. So, why call it an upset?  Am I missing something? Is it really earth-shattering Thiem beating Nadal (or Roger or Djoker)?

snippet.textDisplay: Something is wrong with the entire Australian Open. Great control players like Federer, Nadal, Wawrinka, are inordinately hitting long, into the net and mis-hitting. I think it may be the balls prescribed for the tournament, however, from the serve speeds, they seem to be of correct weight and bounce. Maybe it is the fleece on them, or maybe the surface of the court was doctored in some way. In any case none of the great players are hitting according to their normal patterns. I think the tournament leaders did it to throw a greater measure of chance into the tournament, to give a better opportunity to lower tier players to win.

snippet.textDisplay:
Sad for Rafa. Happy for Thiem. Knew it was going to be a tough match for both. As stated before, this remaining half was going to be painful, because 4 guys I like will face each other. Rafa deserves some rest after that non off-season he had. Likely won’t play till Acapulco.

Onward to Semis. We will see if that extra day will give Federer the boost he needs against Djokovic, as Djokovic has the upper hand currently due to form and more routine wins. Thiem will also need to be rested if he is to give Zverev a challenge as Zverev has had simpler matches. Hope neither Semis will be blowouts.
